# Security Rules

Core requirement: Dealer A must never access Dealer B data.

## Data Isolation

- Every dealership-owned table includes `dealership_id`.
- Backend derives `dealership_id` from authenticated user context.
- Supabase RLS must enforce dealership isolation when database is added.
- Support admin access must be explicitly controlled and audit logged.

## Credentials

- Provider API credentials encrypted and stored server-side only.
- Never commit `.env` or real secrets.
- Use `.env.example` for documentation only.

## Roles

- `owner` — billing, settings, users
- `manager` — vehicles, tags, inventory sources
- `lot_staff` — pair, reassign, unpair tags
- `viewer` — read-only dashboard
- `support_admin` — internal LotSync support with full audit logging

## Audit Events

Log: login, vehicle CRUD, price changes, source sync, tag pair/reassign/unpair, manual push, provider failures, permission changes.
